    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.15.12"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">215 Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">12</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">GRANT FOREMAN
                        <lb/>
                    1419 WEST OKMULGEE AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    MUSKOGEE, OKLAHOMA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>November 8, 1930.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am very grateful to you for your kind review of my book <hi rend="underline">Indians and Pioneers</hi> in the issue of the Post-Dispatch for October 18. I am glad that you recognize as I do, an interesting field here for historical research and writing. I have given up the practice of the law in order to devote the remainder of my days of usefulness to discovering and making available to others the history of this region.</p> 
                
                <p>I am having sent to you another book, the Journal of Gen. Ethan Allen Hitchcock who spent the riper years of his life in St. Louis and died there in 1870. During his active service in the army he was stationed there.</p>
                
                <p>I trust you will have leisure to examine the book and that you will find it worthy a mention in your columns.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Grant Foreman</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis Post Dispatch</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis, Missouri.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial">In&#8212; <hi rend="underline">Indians and Pioneers</hi> &#8212; Grant Foreman 
                    Yale <hi rend="caps">U.</hi> Press 1930</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
